<paragraph blockId="1.[189,1398,1964,2025]" lastBlockId="2.[187,1399,1263,1399]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,408,1964,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erectifolia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,408,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Sonerila erectifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[413,500,1965,1991]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[641,846,1964,1990]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violifolia">
<emphasis box="[641,846,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Sonerila violifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in its scorpioid or subumbelliform inflorescence, but it differs in the length of stem (ca 
<quantity box="[616,672,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" unit="cm" value="1.0">1 cm</quantity>
long in 
<taxonomicName authority="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane, 2021" authorityName="Phonepaseuth &amp; Souladeth &amp; Souvannakhoummane &amp; Vongthavone &amp; Tagane" authorityYear="2021" box="[764,910,1998,2025]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="erectifolia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[764,910,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">S. erectifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[915,1003,1999,2025]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
vs 
<quantity box="[1040,1155,1998,2025]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.4" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" unit="cm" value="14.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“18 cm</quantity>
long in 
<taxonomicName box="[1247,1380,1998,2025]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Sonerila" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="violifolia">
<emphasis box="[1247,1380,1998,2025]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">S. violifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the venation of the leaves (2 veins running from the base of lamina vs pinnately veined with 2â€“3 lateral primary veins), hairiness of leaves (sparsely covered with whitish hairs on veins abaxially vs glabrous), the length of the petiole (
<quantity box="[434,536,1335,1362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" unit="cm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“10 cm</quantity>
long vs 
<quantity box="[631,717,1335,1362]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="1.0">1â€“7 cm</quantity>
long), and number of flowers per inflorescence (5â€“12(â€“18) flowers vs 1â€“9 flowers). For further comparison see 
<tableCitation box="[802,890,1372,1398]" captionStart="Table 1" captionStartId="2.[189,258,265,291]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Table 1. Comparison of Sonerila erectifolia Phonep., Soulad. &amp; Tagane sp. nov. and S. violifolia Hook.f. ex Triana. 1 = from Renner et al. 2001." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/DF29FB9A2414FFA8FF79222AFD204D64" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" tableUuid="DF29FB9A2414FFA8FF79222AFD204D64">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
