<subSubSection lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,334,264,290]" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,264,290]" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[189,1398,311,373]" lastBlockId="5.[187,1400,265,751]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="141" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">
Herbs acaulescent or with a short rhizomatous stem, 10â€“14(â€“20) cm tall including inflorescences. 
<emphasis box="[1299,1398,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="140">Rhizome</emphasis>
cylindrical, 
<quantity box="[332,421,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" unit="cm" value="2.5" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="2.0">2â€“3 cm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity box="[544,658,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“10 mm</quantity>
in diam, covered with long blonde hairs, hairs 
<quantity box="[1230,1329,346,373]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="140" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3â€“4 mm</quantity>
long. 
<emphasis box="[189,271,266,291]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Leaves</emphasis>
simple, forming a basal rosette, erect; lamina elliptic-oblong, ovate-elliptic, 4â€“6 Ã— 
<quantity box="[1278,1393,265,292]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2â€“2.5 cm</quantity>
, membranous, green, sparsely covered with whitish hairs on margin and tip adaxially, pale green, sparsely covered with whitish hairs on veins abaxially, apex mucronate or rounded, base cuneate or attenuate (to truncate), margin finely crenate and sparsely long ciliate, with 2 pairs of primary lateral veins arising from base of lamina; petiole 
<quantity box="[537,641,406,433]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="8.0" valueMax="10.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“10 cm</quantity>
long, light green to reddish-brown, sparsely covered with long pale green hairs. 
<emphasis box="[384,539,442,468]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Inflorescence</emphasis>
terminal, scorpioid cyme or subumbelliform cymes, 5â€“12(â€“18)-flowered; peduncle 
<quantity box="[304,423,477,504]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="cm" value="12.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="10.0">10â€“15 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[501,622,477,504]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.0">2â€“2.5 mm</quantity>
in diam., glabrous to sparsely hairy. 
<emphasis box="[1070,1147,478,503]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Bracts</emphasis>
minute. 
<emphasis box="[1253,1399,477,503]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Hypanthium</emphasis>
cylindrical, 
<quantity box="[327,423,513,539]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="8.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="8.5" valueMax="9.0" valueMin="8.0">8â€“9 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[493,559,513,539]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
in diam., reddish brown, glabrous, Calyx lobes 3 (or rarely 4), triangular, ca 1 Ã— 
<quantity box="[266,358,548,575]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="2.5">2.5 mm</quantity>
, apex short acuminate; pedicel 
<quantity box="[725,837,548,574]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" metricValueMax="12.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="9.0" valueMax="12.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“12 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[910,1029,548,574]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="0.95" valueMax="1.0" valueMin="0.9">0.9â€“1 mm</quantity>
in diam., glabrous. 
<emphasis box="[1262,1335,548,574]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Petals</emphasis>
3 (or rarely 4), elliptic-oblong, 9â€“11 Ã— 
<quantity box="[576,675,583,610]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5â€“6 mm</quantity>
, pinkish purple to light pink, rarely white adaxially, pearl pink abaxially tinged with dark pink along midvein. 
<emphasis box="[736,834,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Stamens</emphasis>
3 (or rarely 4), anthers lanceolate, 
<quantity box="[1237,1333,619,645]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="7.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="7.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="7.0">7â€“8 mm</quantity>
long, curved, basally inflated and deeply cordate, bright yellow; filaments 
<quantity box="[979,1074,654,680]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.0" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="6.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="7.0" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="6.0">6â€“8 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous, usually pale pink. 
<emphasis box="[255,328,690,716]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Ovary</emphasis>
3-locular (or rarely 4), ellipsoid, style 
<quantity box="[781,907,689,716]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="141" unit="mm" value="12.0" valueMax="13.0" valueMin="11.0">11â€“13 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous, pale pink, sometimes pale green to white, stigma capitate, glabrous, white. 
<emphasis box="[758,830,725,750]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Fruits</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[887,954,725,751]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="141">Seeds</emphasis>
not seen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
